# FOOD TRUCK ACTIVATION KIT B — WALKTHROUGH COPY
## Owner-Facing Screen-by-Screen Copy
### SEG-KIT-B · Bishop Sonnet 4.6 · Statute §3 · 2026-06-10

---

## §0 — Voice + Visual Constraints (Knight implementation notes)

**Purpose:** These rules govern every screen in the
RedCarpetWalkthrough component. Knight: apply them uniformly.
Do not override for any individual screen.

**Voice:**
- Sentence case only. No ALL CAPS words or phrases.
- No em-dashes. Use a comma, period, or line break instead.
- Plain English. If a food truck owner wouldn't say the word
  on a Tuesday, cut it.
- Owner is the subject of every call-to-action.
  "Add your menu" not "Menu can be added."
- Warmth comes from honesty, not exclamation marks.
  One exclamation mark is allowed per full flow. Use it wisely.

**Layout:**
- Mobile-first. Max content width: 375px safe zone.
- 80-character line limit for all copy blocks.
- Each screen carries exactly one primary decision.
  Secondary actions are visually subordinate.
- Progressive disclosure: don't front-load information.
  Owner earns the next screen by clicking through the last one.

**Loading and feedback (canons, no exceptions):**
- Every button triggers a visible state change on tap.
  Minimum: spinner + button text change to "Working..."
- Any async operation over 3 seconds shows a progress
  indicator with specific copy (see §9).
- Stripe redirect gets a named loading state, not a blank screen.
- Post-checkout webhook wait gets a heartbeat indicator.

**Accessibility:**
- Tap targets: minimum 44x44px.
- Color contrast: WCAG AA minimum.
- Every interactive element has an accessible label.

