## §9 — Long-Running Progress States

*Per BP078 canon: any operation over 3 seconds wall-clock*
*must show a progress indicator with specific copy.*
*"Loading..." is not acceptable. Name what is happening.*

---

### Stripe redirect (loading state)

**Trigger:** primary CTA tap on Screen 3 or Screen 5.
**Expected duration:** 2 to 6 seconds.

**Loading copy:**
```
Opening your secure checkout. Just a moment.
```

**Progress indicator:** spinner + copy above.

**Fallback (over 8 seconds):**
```
Stripe is taking a little longer than usual.
Still working. Do not close this screen.
```
*(16 words)*

---

### Post-checkout webhook wait (Screen 6 entry)

**Trigger:** return from Stripe after successful payment.
**Expected duration:** 3 to 10 seconds for webhook confirmation.

**Loading copy:**
```
Confirming your membership. This takes just a few seconds.
```

**Progress indicator:** animated step indicator showing
"Payment received" checkmark + "Activating membership..." spinner.

**Fallback (over 15 seconds):**
```
This is taking a little longer than expected.
Your payment went through. We are confirming membership.
If this screen does not advance, text <Founder phone>.
```
*(28 words including contact line. Acceptable: this is a
money moment and needs the contact fallback.)*

Knight: at 15 seconds, if webhook has not fired,
also trigger a background email to Founder alerting
to the delayed confirmation so he can manually verify.
This is a human-safety net, not a band-aid.

---

### Walkthrough initial load (cue card data fetch)

**Trigger:** owner opens the cue card URL or scans QR.
**Expected duration:** 1 to 4 seconds.

**Loading copy:**
```
Loading your invitation from <introducer name>...
```

If introducer name is unknown at load time:
```
Loading your invitation...
```

**Fallback (over 6 seconds):**
```
Taking a little longer than usual. Almost there.
```

---

### Menu setup save (Screen 6, "Set up your menu" flow)

**Trigger:** owner taps save on any menu item.
**Expected duration:** 1 to 3 seconds.

**Loading copy:**
```
Saving your menu item...
```

**Fallback (over 5 seconds):**
```
Save is taking a moment. Your item is not lost.
Still working.
```

